{
  "texts": [
    "By definition the weights sum to one, so we have",
    "where 1 is the vector with all entries one.",
    "The first term, 1 T w, is the total weight on the non-cash assets, and we refer to it as the total asset weight.",
    "The cash weight is one minus the total asset weight, i.e., c = 1 -1 T w.",
    "Several portfolio types can be expressed in terms of the holdings."
  ]
}